{{refimprove|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox organization | image = | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = | map_size = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | map_alt = <!-- map alt text --> | motto = Transforming Africa's Agriculture | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | formation = 1967 | extinction = <!-- {{End date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | type = [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = Agricultural research and development | professional_title = <!-- for professional associations --> | headquarters = Ibadan, Oyo State, Nigeria | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using {{Coord}} --> | services = Providing better living for the rural farmers | language = ALL | leader_title = Director General | leader_name = Nteranya Sanginga | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = Board of Trustees | parent_organization = <!-- or | parent_organisation = , if one --> | subsidiaries = | affiliations = [[CGIAR]] | budget = | slogan = | remarks = | footnotes = | name = International Institute of Tropical Agriculture | native_name = | former_name = | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | map_caption = | map2 = | abbreviation = IITA | founder = <!-- or | founders = --> | merger = | location = | region_served = Africa | membership = CGIAR | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = http://www.iita.org }}
The '''International Institute of Tropical Agriculture''' ('''IITA''') works with partners to enhance crop quality and productivity, reduce producer and consumer risks, and generate wealth from agriculture, with the ultimate goals of reducing hunger, malnutrition, and poverty. IITA's research-for-development (R4D) focuses on addressing the development needs of tropical countries. The institute was established in 1967 and is headquartered in [[Ibadan]], [[Nigeria]], with several research stations across [[Africa]]. IITA is a nonprofit organization governed by a Board of Trustees, supported by several countries and the [[Consultative Group on International Agricultural Research]] (CGIAR).
==History== IITA was established in 1967 in Ibadan, the idea of the institute came from [[Ford Foundation|Ford]] and [[Rockefeller Foundation|Rockefeller]] foundations desire to establish a centre for the improvement in quality of tropical foods.<ref>Mohan, R. D. R., International Institute of Tropical Agriculture, Symposium on Sustainable Food Production in Sub-Saharian Africa, & Symposium on "Sustainable Food Production in Sub-Saharian Africa". (1992). Sustainable food production in sub-Saharian Africa: [symposium on "Sustainable Food Production in Sub-Saharian Africa", being held at IITA headquarters at Ibadan, Nigeria, in December 1992]. Ibadan: International Institute of Tropical Agriculture. P. 2</ref> The institute came to existence with the enactment of decree 32. of 1967. Part of the institute's initial goals were to develop a better productive farming system, the selection and breeding of high yielding crop varieties that are resistant to diseases and pest and strengthening agricultulral research in the humid and tropic regions. The institute was initially situated on a 1000 hectare land. The institute focused on a cereal improvement program, grain and legumes improvement program, farming systems and root and tuber improvement program. The grain and [[legume]] improvement system consisted of [[soybean]], [[cowpea]] and tuber program composed of [[Yam (vegetable)|yam]] and [[cassava]].<ref>Coker Onita. (1987). IITA and Massive Production of Food. Spear Focus, Spear Magazine, P. 4-7</ref> IITA joined CGIAR in 1971. It later added tree products such as plantain and banana.
